pageContext.claim: “So now Comey’s admitting he was wrong. Wow, but he’s only doing so because he got caught red handed. He was actually caught a long time ago. So what are the consequences for his unlawful conduct. Could it be years in jail? Where are the apologies to me and others, Jim?”
pageContext.analysis: Comey admitted he was "overconfident" when he defended his former agency's use of the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act (FISA) and said of the Inspector General report: "He's right, I was wrong." But the report did not allege any "unlawful conduct" by Comey, as the errors occurred mostly at the agent level.
